-- IJM Land jumps on takeover offer from parent company
-- By Yantoultra Ngui
-- Mon Jun 09, 2014 09:49PM EDT
-- None



KUALA LUMPUR, June 10 (Reuters) - Shares of Malaysia's property firm IJM Land Bhd <IJML.KL> rose as much as 9.4 percent after its parent IJM Corp Bhd <IJMS.KL> announced a plan to take it private in a deal worth $620 million. [ID:nL4N0OQ38L]

The shares were 7.8 percent higher at 3.47 ringgit per share as of 0111 GMT.  The proposal values IJM Land at 3.55 ringgit per share.   ($1 = 3.1970 Malaysian Ringgit)